<Author>SFGlen
<Content>Fantastic! What a Find! My partner and I enjoyed 5 incredible days at his wonderful hotel, in Sept/Oct 08, and had the time of our lives! I've been to Amsterdam , (from San Francisco), many, many times, and have stayed at a variety of straight and gay hotels - some high end and some less so. The Black Tulip is the BEST.We had Room 12, which others have reviewed poorly. It must have been recently updated, because we found the room impeccibly clean, beautifully appointed, very spacious for Amsterdam, and with everything working perfectly. The shower  tub felt fantastic, after a late night of party! The room is just charming, creaking floor and all, AND has the benefit of being on the ground level, so no lugging heavy suitcases up those steep Dutch stairs! We LOVED it!The hosts at the Black Tulip are great - friendly and welcoming as you get settled, ready to easily answer any questions, make recommendations, and so forth. Although they must go throug the routine several times a day, we never felt like we were being processed. Actually, we felt like we had local friends. We actually ran into them around town and had a friendly drink together.Breakfast is served late. It's about time someone thought of that. I can't tell you how many times I've missed breakfast, at other venues, because you just tend to sleep late in Amsterdam :) And, by the way, this was no serve yourself buffet. The hosts are great cooks and make your meal to order, after serving you coffee and fresh-baked breads. We looked forward to it, and to mingling with other guests, (who you would not otherwise see), every morning.On our day of departure, which was quite early, they even got up early to prepare a meal just for us. That was really above and beyond service and we actually felt guilty about saying no thank you.Overall, a great and memorable experience. Thank you so much. 
