<Author>Dakotah1
<Content>Live a little at the Tulip My wife and I just returned from an enjoyable 5 day stay at the Black Tulip in early September 2008. The Black Tulip is a great place to stay while exploring Amsterdam. The hotel is only a short walk from centraal station which offers access to all of the trains, trams, buses, and canal boats for easy touring of the city. Onno and Jurrich are great hosts who are responsive to your needs without being overbearing. We were offered a cold beverage during check-in followed by Jurrich's map tour of Amsterdam highlighting many off the favorite attractions. Breakfast was casual and enjoyable with fresh fruit, fresh pressed coffee or tea and a typical European selection of cheeses, meats, and baked goods highlighted by cooked to order eggs. We met wonderful people from Wales, South Africa, and the States during our stay. Breakfast is served from 10-12am which is nice following a late or busy night.Our vanilla nonsmoking double room faced the quiet canal and featured a very nicely remodeled bath with top notch fixtures. We would definitely stay here again when we return to Amsterdam. We might even stretch our comfort zone a little with an upgrade to one of the specialty rooms! 
