ay of appointments certainly stretched our imagination. They are worth seeing and used I supposed.鈻玈ense of safety and securitySafety and security was explained to us at the time of check-in. We were responsible for our guests and the building was monitored 24 hour by CCTV, placed at strategic locations throughout the hotel. This was very good. We felt very safe. 鈻獴reakfast time (BT)This was truly one of the many highlights of our holiday. BT was very family oriented and the conversation around the table was just informative and stimulating. Fan-tas-tic! This was very fascinating as we were all strangers from different part of the globe. Guest shared their world experiences in just an amazing fashion. You sit at the table forever. Even the staff joined in at times. By the way, breakfast was served buffet style. We called it the Continent Breakfast with and 鈥榯hat edge鈥? The food items were fresh; we even believe the bread came directly from the bakery. Our breakfast chef was always at hand to prepare egg dishes to our liking, in front of our very own eyes. Delicious! We loved his scrambled eggs. That master piece above the rectangular breakfast table 鈥?鈥榳icked stuff鈥? We will definitely be staying at the Black Tulip Hotel when we next visit Amsterdam. It is an affordable base, with great staff. A lot going for Black Tulip. Highly recommend. Z/N 
